President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. The nominees include Richard Buckius for Deputy Director of the National Science Foundation, T.F. Scott Darling III for Administrator of the Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration, Linda Etim for Assistant Administrator for the Bureau for Africa at the United States Agency for International Development, Laura S.H. Holgate for United States Representative to the Vienna Office of the United Nations and United States Representative to the International Atomic Energy Agency, Marcel Lettre for Under Secretary of Defense for Intelligence, Patrick J. Murphy for Under Secretary of the Army, Cherry A. Murray for Director of the Office of Science at the Department of Energy, and Robert D. Reischauer for Member of the Board of Trustees of the Social Security Trust Funds. President Obama expressed his gratitude to these individuals for their willingness to serve the American people and looks forward to working with them.